{"annotation":" Napa City, one of the most famous wine regions of USA, is located in California. Pacific Coast and the generous warmth of the sun have made the region attractive for tourists. The main attractions of Napa, of course, will be the estates with precious vineyards and numerous wineries. 
Start your tour from the vineyard and wine cellar Hess Collection. In addition to the tasting of fine wines, here you can take a walk through the Art Museum. 
Tourists will definitely love: 

 - extravagant wine estates-factories Opus One, Stags' Leap Winery, Robert Mondavi Winery, and other; 
 - Museum di Rosa, which presents exhibitions of contemporary art; 
 - natural zone of the Skyline Wilderness Park with rich vegetation and ponds; 
 - Alston Park, where dog owners with their pets go for a walk regularly; 
 - horse riding from the Horse Company; 
 - performances, held in theaters: The Uptown Theatre and Opera House; 
 - territory of Riverbend Plaza, where many cozy shops and cafes are concentrated. 
 - Golf enthusiasts can choose for themselves one of several high-quality golf courses. 
 - Have you still not decided where to spend your vacation? Napa – the best solution for a comfortable holiday with your family. ","map":"place/united-states,california,napa"}

{"annotation":" New Orleans (United States) is a gem of Louisiana, jewelry rim of which can be considered as Lake Pontchartrain, the Mississippi River and the Gulf of Mexico.
Main street Magazine Street is a local sight. The most famous district here – French Quater. Dozens of clubs, restaurants, museums and entertaining shops are concentrated here. Bourborn Street is considered as a heart of the French Quarter.
Several attractions, which are in high demand among tourists, can be identified: 
 - ancient cemetery Saint Louis, which gained disrepute because of ghosts, living here; 
 - bridge-dam (38.5 miles) across Lake Pontchartrain; 
 - Jackson Square; 
 - the territory of New Orleans Mint; 
 - museums: New Orleans Museum of Art, Contemporary Arts Center, Ogden Museum of Southern Art; 
 - Audubon State Park. 
 - Old buildings are located in a residential area of Uptown. Here is the Audubon Zoo. 
 The city is famous for its energetic nightlife, club entertainment, and availability of alcohol, lights the numerous casinos, which have filled in excess the Faubourg Marigny district. 
Doors of beautiful and hospitable tourist center are open to guests. Come here, if only to listen to real jazz. Because New Orleans is its historic homeland! 
","map":"place/united-states,louisiana,new-orleans"}

{"annotation":" Oahu Island, which is part of the web of the Hawaiian archipelago, is notable for tourists for its exotic nature and pristine beaches. In the southeastern part of the coast there is the city of Honolulu – the capital of Hawaii. Considerable amount of Oahu attractions is collected on this territory.
You should start your journey from the museum, the former residence of the royal couple Kalakaua and Liliuokalani with the unusual name Iolani.
Polynesian Cultural Center has prepared for visitors plenty of entertainment in the form of performances and cooperative handmade art. Here is an ethnographic museum.
You can admire from a distance the huge crater of an extinct volcano Diamond Head. If you take a chance and climb to its top, then Honolulu will appear in all its glory before the daredevil.
Then it is desirable to walk through the cemetery “Valley of the Temples” with a 3-meter statue of Buddha, admire the statue of King Kamehameha in front of the building of Supreme Court and climb to the observation deck of the Aloha Tower – Hawaiian lighthouse.
Besides these attractions guests should pay their attention to:

 - aquarium in the tourist district of Waikiki, located along a coral reef; 
 - Honolulu Zoo, home for more than 1,200 species of animals; 
 - Chinatown Market with Asian delicacies; 
 - numerous monuments and memorials. 
 The rich nature of the island, expressed by tropical forests, mountain ranges, deep canyons, waterfalls and sandy beaches, flavoured with architectural and cultural attractions – a great reason to visit Oahu. Welcome to Hawaii!
","map":"place/united-states,hawaii,o-ahu"}
